# INKs Official License  
**Version 1.0 — Doctor-G / @giggiart / INKs on Chain**

---

## 1. Artist Rights
- The artist retains full moral and copyright ownership of all original artworks, including attribution, integrity, exhibition, and promotional rights.  
- The holder of the digital asset does **not** automatically acquire the author’s copyright or moral rights over the work.  
- Source reference: https://www.inksonchain.xyz

---

## 2. Collector Rights
The on-chain holder of an INK is granted:

- A **limited personal and commercial license** to use, display, reproduce, or sell physical or digital products incorporating the artwork, provided that:
  - Proper attribution is always given (“Artwork by Doctor-G, INKs on Chain”)
  - The usage is **not** illegal, defamatory, harmful, or damaging to the reputation of the artist or the project.
- A **commercial extended license** (for holders owning ≥ 3 INKs or participating in the Collector / Creator / Partner program) may be requested, allowing branding, merchandise, and derivative production upon written approval or tokenized access.

---

## 3. Derivatives, Remix, and Adaptations
- Remixing or derivative works are allowed **only** when clearly credited as “Inspired by INKs” and linked back to the original collection.  
- Derivatives must respect the INKs visual and narrative tone. Political, hateful, pornographic, or discriminatory uses are strictly forbidden.  
- AI reinterpretations, 3D conversions, or other modifications are permitted **for personal use only** and cannot be monetized or re-minted as new NFT collections without prior written consent.

---

## 4. Trademarks & Branding
- The names **“INKs”**, **“giggiart”**, and **“Doctor-G MadLab”**, along with their logos and emblems, are proprietary trademarks of @giggiart.  
- They may not be used on websites, social media, or merchandise in ways implying official affiliation without explicit authorization.  
- Descriptive uses such as “Personal collection of INKs” are allowed.

---

## 5. Royalties & Artist Support
- Royalties set on official marketplaces (e.g. Trio, Magic Eden, Gamma) must remain active and not be circumvented.  
- A standard tip (≈ 2%) supports future seasons, customization tools, and ecosystem development.

---

## 6. License Revocation
Violation of any section of this license may result in immediate revocation of commercial rights and potential legal action by Doctor-G MadLab.

---

## 7. Transfer of Rights
When an INK is sold or transferred, its corresponding license (personal or commercial) is automatically transferred to the new on-chain holder.  
Extended commercial licenses must be re-issued upon request.

---

## 8. Acceptance
By purchasing, holding, or using an INK, you accept these IP & Commercial Use terms.  
Ownership of an INK grants the right to use and monetize **that single piece**, not the entire INKs universe or brand.

